Suggested file layout

Keep it simple.

border_checker/
│
├── main.py
├── fetcher.py
├── parser.py
├── display.py
└── crossings.txt

What each file does

main.py

Runs the project and links everything together.

fetcher.py

Contains:
	•	fetch_data()

parser.py

Contains:
	•	extract_border_rows()
	•	parse_wait_times()
	•	maybe sort_by_wait()

display.py

Contains:
	•	show_results()

crossings.txt

Optional file with your favourite crossings so you can edit without touching code.

Example:

Zosin
Dorohusk
Hrebenne
Korczowa

That is the right move. Keep user-editable values outside the code when possible.

