Best project version for a beginner

Start with version 1:

Version 1 goals
	•	fetch webpage
	•	print raw border rows
	•	no sorting yet
	•	no save file yet

That proves the data pull works.

Version 2 goals
	•	extract crossing name
	•	extract wait time
	•	display clean list

Version 3 goals
	•	sort by shortest wait
	•	highlight best crossing

Version 4 goals
	•	save last results to file
	•	load previous results

That is how you build properly. One layer at a time.

⸻

Why this structure matters

Because otherwise you end up with:
	•	one ugly script
	•	impossible debugging
	•	hard to update when the website changes
	•	no clue what broke

Small functions give you:
	•	cleaner logic
	•	easier debugging
	•	easier upgrades
	•	less chaos

That is how real projects should be built, even small ones.

